-how to convert into string: using '.to_s' method

-how to convert into integer: using '.to_i' method

-how to convert into float: using 'to_f' method

-'gets' is the syntax to get input from user

-'.chomp' method takes of any Enter characters hanging out at the end of our string

-see page: 27

-there are two classes of integers in Ruby: Fixnums and Bignums. Basically, really
big number are Bignums, and smaller ones are Fixnum

-Most programming languages don't have anything like Bignum (at least not built in)
so all of your integers have to be relatively small, and if you add two largish
integers you might end up with a very small one or even a negative one.
